channel.description:
[code]	public boolean containsReadUnsignedShort(ClassGen cg) { //Searches for the 'readUnsignedShort' method in a ClassGen using bytecode iteration
		boolean[] results = new boolean[8];
		for(Method m : cg.getMethods()) {
			byte[] methodBuffer = m.getCode().getCode();
			for(byte b : methodBuffer)
				switch(b) {
					case 0x10: //bipush
						results[0] = true;
					break;
					case 0x08: //#8
						if(results[0])
							results[1] = true;
					break;
					case 0x78: //ishl
						if(results[1])
							results[2] = true;
					break;
					case 0x11: //sipush
						if(results[2])
							results[3] = true;
					break;
					case 0x00: //part of sipush or #255
						if(results[3])
							results[4] = true;
					break;
					case 0xFF: //#255
						if(results[4])
							results[5] = true;
					break;
					case 0x7E: //iand
						if(results[5])
							results[6] = true;
					break;
					case 0x60: //iadd
						if(results[6])
							results[7] = true;
					break;
				}
		return results[7];
	}[/code]
Though you could go a step further and not even use bcel, just read raw from the class and parse out the class data from the file's buffer.
